					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">mog123 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">can you tell me my mistake?</div>
<br />Your mistake was you were not using the file with your color values at all. Although you had the data included in the ROM, you were not using it.
<br />
<br />When you did this:
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp;lda #$00<br />&nbsp;sta $2007</div>
<br />you were always getting color $00 (gray) as the first palette color, completely ignoring the included .pal file. But when you use "lda Palette,x" you're actually loading from the values inside the .pal file, since the label "Palette" points to the part of the ROM where your included palette is.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

